  "enhanced_information": "Cardiomyopathy can be associated with deficiencies in certain nutrients, particularly selenium and zinc. Selenium deficiency is linked to increased oxidative stress and myocardial damage, which can lead to cardiomyopathy. Zinc deficiency may impair immune function and increase inflammation, potentially resulting in heart muscle damage and cardiomyopathy. Phosphorus deficiency disrupts energy metabolism, which can impair cardiac function and contribute to cardiomyopathy. However, the link between boron deficiency and cardiomyopathy is unclear and not well-established. Therefore, the most relevant deficiencies associated with cardiomyopathy are selenium and zinc, with phosphorus also having a potential role."
